The President of the United States, Donald Trump, made remarks at the celebration of Diwali, the Hindu Festival of Lights, at the White House. He expressed his condolences for the devastating wildfires in California and thanked the firefighters and first responders for their courage. Trump also acknowledged the contributions of Americans of Indian and Southeast Asian heritage and recognized several individuals in his administration who are of Indian descent. He mentioned his efforts to improve trade deals with India and praised the country's democracy. The President lit the Diya, a traditional lamp, and wished everyone a happy and joyful Diwali. He then engaged in a brief Q&A session with reporters, where he declined to comment on the replacement of the Department of Homeland Security Secretary and CNN's lawsuit against him.